22 And a sweet melody flowed 23 through the luminous air; whence a good zeal 24 made me reprove the daring of Eve,
25 who there where earth and heaven obeyed, 26 a woman, alone and just then created, 27 did not endure to remain under any veil;
28 under which if she had been devout, 29 I would have felt those ineffable delights 30 earlier and for a longer time.

43 A little farther on, seven trees of gold 44 falsified in appearance the long stretch 45 of the space that was still between us and them;
46 but when I had come so near to them, 47 that the common object, which deceives the sense, 48 did not lose any of its form through distance,
49 the power that rightly furnishes discourse, 50 perceived that they were candelabra, 51 and in the voices of the song ‘Hosanna’.

64 Then I saw people, as if following their leaders,
65 coming behind, dressed in white;
66 and such whiteness was never seen here on earth.

70 When I had reached such a position on my bank, 71 that only the river kept me at a distance, 72 in order to see better I paused my steps,
73 and I saw the little flames going ahead, 74 leaving the air painted behind them, 75 and they had the appearance of drawn brushstrokes;
76 so that above them remained distinct 77 seven bands, all in those colors 78 from which the Sun makes the rainbow and the Moon her halo.

94 Each was winged with six wings;
